text: Diocese or Archdiocese of Chełm may refer to the following ecclesiastical jurisdictions with see at Chełm (Kulm) in southeastern Poland : * the former Roman Catholic Diocese of Chełm, Latin precursor of the suppressed Diocese of Chełm–Lublin and nominally restored as a Latin Catholic titular see * the suppressed Ukrainian Catholic Eparchy of Chełm–Bełz * the Archdiocese of Lublin and Chełm of the Polish Orthodox Church
title: Diocese of Chełm
